TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hao, Jia
AU  - Zheng, Kuncheng
T1  - Effect of the Equity Capital Ratio on the Relationship between Competition and Bank Risk-Taking Behavior
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfab009
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 10
IS  - 4
SP  - 813
EP  - 855
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - We examine how the relationship between competition and risk-taking changes with the ex ante bank equity capital ratio. We show that competition in the banking market, on average, mitigates risk-taking by banks. This relationship, however, can be altered by a bank’s ex ante equity capital ratio. More specifically, when face with increased competition, banks with low ex ante equity capital ratios engage in relatively larger reductions in risk-taking. They do so primarily by decreasing the risk in their lending portfolios. In contrast, banks with high enough ex ante equity capital ratios might not reduce their risk-taking at all. (JEL G21, G32, O16, D40, G18)
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfab009
ER  - 



