TY  - JOUR
AU  - Liang, Lantian
AU  - Williams, Ryan
AU  - Chong Xiao, Steven
T1  - Stock Market Information and Innovative Investment in the Supply Chain
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfaa020
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 10
IS  - 4
SP  - 856
EP  - 894
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - We investigate whether suppliers adjust innovative supply chain investment following stock market signals about customers’ economic prospects. We show that suppliers increase R&amp;D and investment in customer-related patents after positive market reactions to customers’ new product announcements. A battery of falsification tests suggest that spurious factors are unlikely to explain our results. Market signals about customers appear more important when information asymmetry is greater, when suppliers face greater competitive threats, and when suppliers are financially unconstrained. Our evidence suggests that the stock market can be a viable source of information to mitigate supply chain frictions. (JEL G14, G30, L14)
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfaa020
ER  - 



